{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἱκέτ-ης</b>, ου, ὁ, <br /> (ἱκνέομαι) <b>one who comes to seek aid</b> or <b>protection, suppliant</b>; frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] of <b>one who comes to seek for purification after homicide</b>, ἀνὴρ ἱ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.158, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.270, +others: later generally, ἱκέται ἱζόμενοι τοῦ θεοῦ 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.113, compare 5.71; ἱ. σέθεν ἔρχομαι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 5.19, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 634, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.136; ἱ. πατρῴων τάφων [prev. author] 3.59; δέξασθαι ἱκέτην 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 27 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of pilgrims to a healing shrine, ἐγκεκοιμις μένων τῶν ἱκετᾶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 4.951.90 (Epid.); ὑβρίζειν.. εἰς ἱκέτας 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Ir.” p.35 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>] W.:—wrongly explained as <b>protector of suppliants</b> by some Grammars  in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.422. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7715","accentedUnicode":"ἱκέτης","shortDef":"a supplicant","mediumDef":"a supplicant","stepGloss":"a supplicant","stepTransliteration":"hiketēs","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}